With respect to the Canada 125 Corporation (a) how will the federal funds be allocated (b) will any part of the federal allocation be used for salaries or bonuses?
(aXiXii)	the insert was designed and produced using internal SSC resources. Consequently no additional cost outside the government was incurred;
(iii)	the cost of printing the new cheque insert was a approximately $170,000;
(b)	St. Joseph Printing Limited was paid by Supply and Services Canada during March 1992 for printing these inserts;
(c)	approximately 22 million inserts were produced
